    "body": "This includes:\n- use system layout by default\n- prevent building multi- and single-threaded libs when using system layout\n- build multi-threaded libs by default\n- add in symlinks which emulate tagged layout when multithreaded libs are built with system layout (for packages like valgrind which expect the -mt suffix)\n\nThis addresses #710 (reasoning here also suggests that multi-threaded libs will nearly always be suitable as a drop-in replacement for single-threaded libs) and #1820.\n",
